.. _u3b:

U3b
===
- Processed from a transcript (as CNAG_13174)

.. figure:: /../_static/images/snoRNAs/u3_h99_igb.png
   :name: u3_h99_igb
   :align: left
   :width: 1389 px
   :height: 646 px
   :scale: 40%
   :figwidth: 100%

- U3b_boxCDsnoRNA-251nt.
- Sequence is nearly identical to that of the other U3-like snoRNA, :ref:`snR45-U13/U3 <snr45u13>` on chromosome 3.
- The homologue from *Naematelia*\ |nbsp|\ *encephala* (`URS0000D98D81_71784 <TreEncU3_>`_ ) is assigned by Rfam as the small nucleolar RNA U3 (`Rfam RF00012 <RfamU3_>`_).
- No sign of the U3-like sequence being interrupted with an intron as is the case in baker's yeast.

- Orthologue of |ortholog_2|.
- In Tremellomycetes the conserved 5' stemloop comprising ``boxes A'/A`` is much shorter.
- U3 sequences in the 5' 70 nt leader have predicted targets in |targetRNA_2|\ : |target_2|\ , like in *S.*\ |nbsp|\ *cerevisiae* (|target_sc1a|, and |target_sc1b|) where they are part of a pseudo-knot (for an overview see [Marmier-Gourrier-2011]_). In baker's yeast another |targetRNA_2| target, |target_sc2|, and interaction sites in the ETS1, |target_scETS1_1| and |target_scETS1_2|, have been described; these interactions do not seem conserved in *Tremellomycetes*, although ETS1 sequences that could support comparable basepairing with U3 in *Cryptococcus* can be found: |target_4| and |target_5|.  In *Tremellomycetes* the ``box A`` U3-element that would interact with |targetRNA_2| sequence  |target_3| seems absent resulting in a much shorter 5' stemloop comprising only ``box A'`` (whereas in baker's yeast ``box A`` forms also part of this structural element). All these U3 interaction sites  differ from regions around the acetylated C near the 3' end of 18S rRNA, found by snR45. 

- In baker's yeast, apart from U3, snoRNAs snR4 and snR45 contain a leader sequence with base-pairing functionality [Sharma-2017_].
- Functions of U3 and snR45 in yeast might be mixed in *Tremellomycetes* (see :ref:`snR45-U13/U3 <snr45u13>`).
- Alignments:

.. figure:: /../_static/images/snoRNAs/U3all-align.png
   :name: u3all-align
   :align: left
   :width: 3603 px
   :height: 586 px
   :scale: 20%
   :figwidth: 100%

   U3 homologs in *Tremellomycetes*, identical to :ref:`snR45-U13/U3-homologs <snR45-align>`

- R2R-script 'makefig' run as ``bash$ sh makefig``:
  
.. rst-class:: asfootnote

::

        #!/bin/bash
        IN=../u3-r2r-in.sto
        MID=u3_R2R.cons.sto
        OUT=../U3-tremellomycetes_R2R.svg

        # calculate consensus
        r2r --GSC-weighted-consensus $IN $MID 3 0.97 0.9 0.75 4 0.97 0.9 0.75 0.5 0.1
        # create the svg figure

        r2r $MID $OUT
